Conditions:<br />
Gates of the Dead City x 4<br />
<!--102-->Bent on Discovery x 3<br />
<br />
Possessions:<br />
Pale Blade: SoF    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br />
If you bid to go first, use Gamling/Stables to get Eomer&#39;s Spear and Firefoot out, otherwise just use 2 turns with Gamling to get them out.  Basic strategy is to get Aragorn, Arwen, and the token conditions (Border Patrol + Uncertain Future) out ASAP, then use Eomer and Aragorn and Arwen to wade through enemy minions.   <br />
<br />
I chose the token conditions b/c they each have 3 tokens to start off with without having to exert anyone.  Gandalf is there to help with condition and burden removal (not to mention the str bonus), and Eowyn is there to protect against enquea: LoM from taking out a main char.  Sword rack is to catch any rohan possesions that get discarded.  I&#39;m using Anduril, KB to help with potential swarms and to allow use of aragorn&#39;s bow.  <br />
<br />
On the shadow side, the idea is to beat down/slow down the fellowship through exertions caused by Gates of the Dead City.  Use Bent on Discovery and the toil mechanic to exert those enduring Naz and pile on burdens.  Corruption is possible against Ring-bearers with fewer than 10 resistance, though I&#39;ve found corruption happens pretty infrequently with this deck.  Keening Wail rocks in this deck, since you play it in maneuver and can make your Naz exert with it.  This deck has some trouble with choke decks, I&#39;ve found.  <br />
<br />
<br />
This is the first deck I&#39;ve built from the ground up (I&#39;ve copied/modified plenty before).  <br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Thoughts and reviews are very welcome.  Thanks in advance.   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
